th Bill Douglas and Eddie Gomez", "venue": "Weill Recital Hall", "roles": ["double_bass"], "works": [{"t": "Selections (unspecified)", "c": null, "w": "104450"}]}, {"id": "44142", "date": "2007-01-28", "label": "Mika Yoshida, Marimba, and Friends", "venue": "Zankel Hall", "roles": ["double_bass"], "works": [{"t": "Mitsue", "c": "John Wyre", "w": "72600"}, {"t": "Mikarimba", "c": "Bill Douglas", "w": "42032"}, {"t": "Variations on Goldberg's Theme and Dreams", "c": "Johann Sebastian Bach", "w": "72604"}, {"t": "Mika Suite", "c": "Eddie Gomez", "w": "72608"}, {"t": "Rolling Men", "c": "Michiru Oshima", "w": "72601"}, {"t": "Pri Fixe", "c": "Peter John Stoltzman", "w": "72602"}, {"t": "Kebjar-Bali", "c": "William L. Cahn", "w": "6350"}, {"t": "Jubilation", "c": "Bill Douglas", "w": "65798"}]}, {"id": "48985", "date": "2011-01-07", "label": "Mikarimba Madness with Gadd and Gomez", "venue": "Zankel Hall", "roles": ["double_bass"], "works": [{"t": "Selections (unspecified)", "c": null, "w": "104450"}]}, {"id": "50591", "date": "2012-04-04", "label": "Mika Yoshida, Marimba, and Richard Stoltzman, Clarinet", "venue": "Weill Recital Hall", "roles": ["double_bass"], "works": [{"t": "Terra Cotta", "c": "Keith Jarrett", "w": "85693"}, {"t": "Marcos Valle Suite", "c": "Marcos Valle", "w": "85696"}, {"t": "Beco", "c": "Marcos Valle", "w": "85695"}, {"t": "Chanson de l'amour", "c": "Michiru Oshima", "w": "85698"}, {"t": "Marika Groove", "c": "Chick Corea", "w": "85697"}, {"t": "Rhapsody in Blue", "c": "George Gershwin", "w": "85699"}, {"t": "Copland Revisited", "c": "Mike Mainieri", "w": "85700"}]}, {"id": "55734", "date": "2015-11-05", "label": "The Stoltzmans on Clarinet and Marimba: Duo for Love", "venue": "Weill Recital Hall", "roles": ["double_bass"], "works": [{"t": "Marika Groove", "c": "Chick Corea", "w": "85697"}, {"t": "Sea Journey", "c": "Chick Corea", "w": "95061"}]}, {"id": "62979", "date": "2019-06-12", "label": "Mika Stoltzman, Marimba", "venue": "Weill Recital Hall", "roles": ["double_bass"], "works": [{"t": "Marika Groove", "c": "Chick Corea", "w": "85697"}, {"t": "Kaleidoscope", "c": "Clarice Assad", "w": "106467"}, {"t": "Sambata and Jubilation", "c": "Bill Douglas", "w": "106466"}]}], "works_created": [{"t": "Mika Suite", "w": "72608"}, {"t": "Love Letter (to my father)", "w": "3283"}, {"t": "Street Smart", "w": "82832"}, {"t": "Morning Love", "w": "82829"}, {"t": "Delgado", "w": "18224"}], "quotes": [], "about_quotes": [{"speaker": "Gary Burton", "relation": "in music group with", "confidence": 1.0, "evidence": "So Eddie Gomez and Joe Hunt were open at the time. So I called them up and hired them to play a week at a club in Boston... So we drove up there, quickly put together some tunes, playing with Eddie and Joe still at this point.", "doc_title": "Gary Burton — Smithsonian Jazz Oral History", "collection": "si", "url": "https://americanhistory.si.edu/sites/default/files/file-uploader/Gary%20Burton%20NEA%20Jazz%20Master%20Oral%20History%20Interview-1.pdf"}, {"speaker": "Marty Morell", "relation": "in music group with", "confidence": 1.0, "evidence": "Although when I was working with Eddie Gomez and Bill Evans... I used to talk with Eddie sometimes", "doc_title": "Marty Morell interviewed by Monk Rowe, Orlando, Florida, February 24, 2017", "collection": "hamilton", "url": "https://litsdigital.hamilton.edu/collections/object/marty-morell-interviewed-monk-rowe-orlando-florida-february-24-2017"}, {"speaker": "Tom Lellis", "relation": "collaborated with", "confidence": 1.0, "evidence": "I got to open for Bill Evans where I met Eddie Gomez and subsequently recorded with him later", "doc_title": "Tom Lellis interviewed by Monk Rowe, Clinton, New York, July 31, 2007", "collection": "hamilton", "url": "https://litsdigital.hamilton.edu/collections/object/tom-lellis-interviewed-monk-rowe-clinton-new-york-july-31-2007"}, {"speaker": "Tyner McCoy", "relation": "collaborated with", "confidence": 0.95, "evidence": "So you got that rhythm section and then on the other side you’ve got Eddie Gomez and Jack DeJohnette... I think it was a combination--I never let anybody make a total decision to use this guy... I always wanted to do that because I’m physically playing with the guy", "doc_title": "Tyner McCoy — Smithsonian Jazz Oral History", "collection": "si", "url": "https://americanhistory.si.edu/sites/default/files/file-uploader/Tyner-McCoy-Transcription-2020.pdf"}, {"speaker": "Jimmy Owens", "relation": "in music group with", "confidence": 0.95, "evidence": "So, in the Newport Youth Band there are a number of musicians who became professional musicians... The bass player, Eddie Gomez, is around. Of the people who are around now, it’s just Eddie Gomez, baritone saxophonist Ronnie Cuber, and myself, and Michael Benny.", "doc_title": "Jimmy Owens — Smithsonian Jazz Oral History", "collection": "si", "url": "https://amhistory.si.edu/jazz/Owens-Jimmy/Owens_Jimmy_Transcript.pdf"}, {"speaker": "Buckingham", "relation": "collaborated with", "confidence": 0.95, "evidence": "I had Eddie Gomez flying to Nashville from New York... I put out the number charts... Eddie looked at the — now of course Eddie Gomez can play, and he looked at the chart", "doc_title": "Buckingham interviewed by Monk Rowe, 2019", "collection": "hamilton", "url": "https://litsdigital.hamilton.edu/collections/fillius-jazz-archive"}]}